<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#000040">Originally posted by Yodak on 01-28-2000 07:53 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Greetings warriors, I have come to extend an olive branch from the magician's of Norath. I currently play a 50th mage as my primary character, so of course the outcome of this debate is very important to me. The fact that our pets are now going to be getting a fix to allow them to dual wield has me elated and concerned at the same time. First off, let me just say that according to what the designers have said on numerous occasions, mage's are supposed to have the most powerful pets. I don't think that our pets will ever be able to compare with a FS dagger-wielding necro pet in speed, but at least this would close the gap in damage output somewhat. That, however, is a debate for another board. On the other hand, I have to admit that I am concerned with the fact that ANY pet could outdamage a warrior of the same rank. In fact, if you check out some of the posts on the magician board, you will see that I am not alone, we as a community support your ongoing campaign to increase the power of the warrior class in combat. I think that the critical hits and cripiling blows are a step in the right direction, but we all know that they don't happen often enough to really make  that big of a difference. I am not like the idiot that posted above, I DO NOT think all you do is hit the auto-attack key and punch kick/bash when it pops! You are an incredible asset to any group, and I for one have been saved on numerous occasions by the heroic efforts of the group warrior. I have seen warriors willingly sacrifice their lives in order for the rest of the group to escape. That is the stuff of legends guys, and you should be proud that you have chosen the most noble profession (class) in Norath IMHO. In closing let me say this, the mages may get their day in the sun today, but it will only strengthen your position to upgrade the warrior class. PLEASE, don't cry for a nerf of the pet-wielding classes, it won't serve anyone in the long run. It won't make you any better in combat, and it certainly won't help us. Instead let us all unite and FIX YOUR CLASS! I, for one, am 100% behind your efforts, and I will encourage my fellow mages to join the picket lines as well. Just remember; united we stand, divided we fall.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
